title: 2014 Debuts: The full first year of Not Reading anything at all!
description:
"Not Reading Debuts" ( <a href=" http://thepiratebay.se/tag/Not+Reading+Debuts" rel="nofollow" target="_NEW"> http://thepiratebay.se/tag/Not+Reading+Debuts</a>  ) are part of the <a href=" http://thepiratebay.se/tag/Not+Reading" rel="nofollow" target="_NEW"> http://thepiratebay.se/tag/Not+Reading</a>  project, and contain all first issues published and/or released during a given month that made an uploader's personal cut. Except not, because this is the annual digest of said packs, containing everything published this year for each month's single most favourite new title. Well, except for the January pick being new, because I only started the Monthlies in February. Plus, I totally failed to narrow it down to a single selection for June - making a body choose between Ellis, Gillen, and Naifeh would just be too cruel, yes? :P

Cover:     <a href=" http://gesserit.000space.com/meta/yuq/users/29/766/PYjTcB5lfV.png" rel="nofollow" target="_NEW"> http://gesserit.000space.com/meta/yuq/users/29/766/PYjTcB5lfV.png</a>

Contains:   Tart           #1-4 (January)   | The Mercenary Sea       #1-8 (February)
            Veil           #1-5 (March)     | Shutter                 #1-7 (April)
            The Woods      #1-8 (May)       | Princess Ugg            #1-6 (June)
            Trees          #1-7 (June)      | The Wicked + the Divine #1-6 (June)
            Ragnarok       #1-3 (July)      | Low                     #1-5 (August)
            Wild's End     #1-4 (September) | The ZooHunters          #0-2 (October)
            Tooth and Claw #1-2 (November)  | Squarriors              #1   (December)

          - 1 concluded and 13+1 continuing works, comprising a grand total of 4
            trade volumes and 49+3 regular and 1 preview issues.
          - Series written by Kurt Busiek, Warren Ellis, Kieron Gillen, Ted
            Naifeh, Greg Rucka, Walt Simonson, Rick Remender, and others.
          - 1 title published by each of Aspen, Dark Horse, Devil's Due, IDW, and
            Oni, 2 from Boom Studios, and a full half-dozen from the undisputed,
            unparalleled, and unsurprising winner... you-know-in-whose-Image!
